title.narrative: OUTPUT 1.1: NUTRITION

description.narrative: Output 1.1 Nutrition: Regional and national stakeholders have increased evidence, capacity and effective platforms to develop and monitor policies and programmes that address inequities in all forms of child malnutrition, including in fragile and humanitarian contexts., which contributes to Child Health, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition, Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Harnessing Power Of Business And Markets, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: OUTCOME 1: Girls, boys and adolescents in LAC benefit from equitable policies and programmes to guarantee their health, wellbeing and full development.
